We now include the local-hostname in the instance metadata for each network interface even when dns hostnames are disabled for a VPC. We also now include an empty public-hostname when there is no public IP for an instance.

From an instance the following can be used to find interface macs and then verify their details:

{code}
# curl http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/network/interfaces/macs/; echo 
{code}

{code}
# curl http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/network/interfaces/macs/06:79:74:4a:f8:6d/local-hostname; echo
{code}
